<title>Chemistry End of Chapter Exercises</title>
<exercise id="fs-idm83460880">
<problem id="fs-idm70201056">
<para id="fs-idp55706368">Give the hybridization of xenon in each of the following. You may wish to review the chapter on the advanced theories of covalent bonding.</para>
<para id="fs-idp145778640">(a) XeF<sub>2</sub></para>
<para id="fs-idp34156544">(b) XeF<sub>4</sub></para>
<para id="fs-idm94340928">(c) XeO<sub>3</sub></para>
<para id="fs-idm79499872">(d) XeO<sub>4</sub></para>
<para id="fs-idp89549968">(e) XeOF<sub>4</sub></para>
</problem>
<solution id="fs-idp15948528">
<para id="fs-idp28786176">(a) <emphasis effect="italics">sp</emphasis><sup>3</sup><emphasis effect="italics">d</emphasis> hybridized; (b) <emphasis effect="italics">sp</emphasis><sup>3</sup><emphasis effect="italics">d</emphasis><sup>2</sup> hybridized; (c) <emphasis effect="italics">sp</emphasis><sup>3</sup> hybridized; (d) <emphasis effect="italics">sp</emphasis><sup>3</sup> hybridized; (e) <emphasis effect="italics">sp</emphasis><sup>3</sup><emphasis effect="italics">d</emphasis><sup>2</sup> hybridized;</para>
</solution>
</exercise>
